==Finnish==
===Etymology===
Originally the so-called weak suffixal gradation form of the partitive suffix ''[[-ta#Finnish|-ta]]'', /ða/ or /ðæ/.

===Case suffix===
'''-a''' (''in words with back vowel harmony'')

'''-ä''' (''in words with front vowel harmony'')

#A suffix for the [[partitive]] case.

====Usage notes====
*This suffix is used after a short vowel or the plural marker ''-j-''.

===See also===
*[[-ta#Finnish|-ta]]
*[[-tta]]

[[Category:Finnish suffixes|a]]
